The paper deals with data imputation, which is a common problem in databases (cs.DB). The authors propose using web-based information to fill in missing values, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.AI). The use of graph models is also a key aspect of the proposed approach, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
